{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0655fa10043ce8674c947ce8b3d5f837","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about what happens when a Claude .jsonl session file is deleted, and the next `claude_consult` is called for that session. I already answered this earlier in the conversation, but let me give another concise answer since we're in a fresh context.\n\nThe path is:\n1. `claude_consult` tool in tools.ts → `ConsultService.consult`\n2. → `resolveRoute` with the explicit session_id\n3. → `sessionFileExists` check on the claude_session_id (checking for the .jsonl file)\n4. → if missing: `markSessionOrphaned`, build bootstrap context, return null session\n\n\n5. → `invokeWithRouteLock` sees null session → `invokeClaude` (no --resume)\n6. → new Claude session created with bootstrap context injected\n7. → `was_orphan_recovery = true` logged in session_events\n","signature":"f109668cc36b293e0ec436a01a15d01c0267ec4ba47df9a3e49548b71353ddb2"}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":112314,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","uuid":"2d2b2ef7-4ab9-4c83-b43c-b5931e947d6a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0655fa10043ce8674c947ce8b3d5f837","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe orphan detection path:\n\n1. **`claude_consult`** with explicit `session_id` → `ConsultService.consult` (`src/consult.ts:52`)\n\n2. **`resolveRoute`** (`src/consult.ts:250`) sees `sessionId` is provided → fetches session from DB, checks project membership\n\n3. **`sessionFileExists`** check (`src/claude.ts:104-122`) — looks for:\n   - `~/.claude/sessions/<claude_session_id>.json`\n   - `~/.claude/sessions/<claude_session_id>.jsonl`\n   - recursively in `~/.claude/projects`\n   \n   File missing → returns `false`\n\n4. **Mark orphaned** (`src/consult.ts:273-282`):\n   - `db.markSessionOrphaned(session.id)` → sets DB status to `orphaned`\n   - `db.getSessionView(session.id)` → loads compact context from registry\n   - Returns route with `selectedSession: null`, `bootstrapContext`, `wasOrphanRecovery: true`\n\n5. **`invokeWithRouteLock`** (`src/consult.ts:97-115`) sees `route.selectedSession === null` → calls `invokeClaude` directly (no `--resume` flag)\n\n6. **New session created** (`src/consult.ts:154-162`) with:\n   - Fresh internal `id`\n   - New `claudeSessionId` from the new Claude process\n   - Bootstrap context injected into the prompt\n\n7. **`session_events`** row written with `event_type: \"orphan_recovery\"`, `was_orphan_recovery: 1`\n\n**Result:** The deleted session is marked `orphaned` in SQLite, a new Claude session is created, and the old registry context (topic, summary, decisions, files, tags, aliases) is injected as bootstrap into the new session's prompt."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":112314,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","uuid":"788f3dfe-29b5-48cc-b449-2a4f211e8776"}
